    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nCythonize glob input assumes unix path separator. This assumption breaks when using `os.path.join` on windows.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/6414a07ec88b60d604daf0e51fd850ee974afdcb/Cython/Build/Dependencies.py#L88\r\n\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\n`os.path.join(path, \"**\", \"*.pyx\")` on windows converts to `f\"{path}\\**\\*.pyx\"`.\r\nWhen passed to `cythonize` the recursive match is not expanded causing files to get missed.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nAll cython files in the path should be found.\r\n\r\n**Environment (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: Windows\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nA workaround to this is to convert the windows path separator to the unix path separator before passing it to `cythonise` but I feel like that should not be required. It took me a while to work out why my files were not getting matched.\r\n",
